The results from raw data in comparison to the standardized data look diffrent from each other . In the raw data, GNI takes almost all of the variation. In the standardized data, the variation is shared between multiple components.We can observe 3 separate groups : - Labo.FM and Parli.F - Ado.Birth and Mat.Mor - Edu.Exp, Life.exp, Edu2.FM, GNI High incomes and education negatively negatively correlate with maternal mortality ratio and the Adolescent birth rate whereas they positively correlate with Life expectancy at birth. The % male and females in the labor force and in representatives in parliament seem to not be associated with incomes and education.

It seems that the type of tea (tea back and/or unpackaged tea) is related to the place where people buy tea. For example, people that buy unpackaged tea would buy tea in tea shop. People that buy tea in chain store and tea shop,would buy both tea bag and unpackaged tea. And people that buy tea bag would buy tea in chain store.
